                <note rend="inline" type="source">365.1121 Slavich, Nickola/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-10T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 10, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 10—8:35
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>172. The Minister of Foreign Affairs and the Chief of the American Section are on
                    leave. Consequently, while I have transmitted the essence of your No. 133, 4th
                    of September, 5 p.m., the replies will not be immediately forthcoming.</p>
                <p>At the Foreign Office I learned that the procedure relative to the detention and
                    imprisonment of foreigners in Italy has been reviewed <pb facs="0757" n="637"
                        xml:id="pg_637"/> by officials of the several Ministries concerned. The
                    final report, however, has not been sent yet to the Ministry of Foreign
                    Affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
